In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 24, 2016, as United Nations Day. He reflects on the progress made since the signing of the United Nations Charter 71 years ago and emphasizes the importance of international cooperation. President Obama highlights the achievements of the United Nations in overcoming the financial crisis, reducing poverty, promoting democracy, and addressing climate change. However, he also acknowledges the challenges that still exist, such as impunity for perpetrators of atrocities, violations of international law, and the plight of refugees. President Obama calls for upholding the values of the United Nations and building a more capable and effective institution to respond to global crises and tackle humanitarian challenges. He pays tribute to the staff and peacekeeping personnel of the United Nations and urges the observance of United Nations Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.